Continue Creating Bridge Table 13


*Using SSIS Toolbox, the following components will be drag in the Control Flow Dashboard:

***Now we will load second bridge table RegionSubRegionBridge***

Step 1: Drag and drop Data Flow Task transformation from the SSIS Toolbox on the right.

Step 2: Double click on Data Flow Task, then drag and drop OLE DB Source.

Step 3: Double click on OLE DB Source. Inside the OLE DB Source Editor, choose SQL Command.

Step 4: Put the below query inside sql command as the source.

select distinct a.RegionName, a.SubRegionName,[USState] , b.Geography, d.CBSA, RCAName, Name
	from [dbo].[RegionSubRegionUSstates] a
	left join [dbo].[FIPS_Moody] b 	on a.USState = b.Geography
	left join [dbo].[MarketToStateMapping] c 	on b.GeoCode = c.USStateCode
    inner  join [dbo].[Vw_AllFips] d 	on c.market = d.CBSA

Step 5: Drag and drop a Data Conversion transformation and double click in it to get into edit mode. Select RegionName and SubRegionName and give a name to Output Alias. Change the Data Type to Unicode string (DT_WSTR) and change the Length to 25 as shown in the screenshot below.






Populated Second Bridge table after executing the package.
